<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="351" pageId="1" pageNumber="350" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1422,793,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis box="[813,1419,793,817]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="350" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,974,793,817]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">Identification.</emphasis>
Our specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moreira, Barbosa &amp; Ribeiro" authorityYear="2012" box="[1209,1330,793,817]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nelsoni">
<emphasis box="[1209,1330,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">M. nelsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are all
</emphasis>
apterous. They were identified based on the body length between 1.70 and 2.00 mm and the pronotum extended posteriorly over almost the entire dorsum of the thorax. In addition, the body is black, with an orange-red mark on the pronotum (Moreira et al. 2012). The distribution of patches of silvery setae on the abdomen is slightly different from the 
<typeStatus box="[1018,1077,1031,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">types</typeStatus>
of this species, but we believe that this represents intraspecific variation only. The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moreira, Barbosa &amp; Ribeiro" authorityYear="2012" box="[1066,1182,1098,1122]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nelsoni">
<emphasis box="[1066,1182,1098,1122]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">M. nelsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that silvery patches occur on the sides of abdominal mediotergites I and 
<collectionCode box="[876,903,1166,1189]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">III</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[917,936,1166,1189]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="1" pageNumber="350" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
, and laterotergites 
<collectionCode box="[1144,1172,1166,1189]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">III</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[1186,1215,1166,1189]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">VI</collectionCode>
, whereas there are no silvery patches centrally on mediotergites 
<collectionCode box="[1305,1325,1200,1223]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="1" pageNumber="350" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
–VIII. In our specimens, there are silvery patches on the sides of
</paragraph>
<caption box="[169,783,2071,2091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350" startId="1.[169,232,2071,2091]" targetBox="[168,1419,1305,2046]" targetPageId="1">
